The paper deals with the problem of computing the maximum volume $j$-simplex inside the convex hull of a given set of points, which is a problem in computational geometry (cs.CG). The algorithm presented involves rounding solutions to a generalization of the $D$-optimal design problem, which is a problem in optimization and statistics (cs.DS). The paper also mentions the problem of finding the principal $j\times j$ submatrix of a positive semidefinite matrix with the largest determinant, which is a problem in numerical linear algebra (cs.NA). The rounding technique used in the algorithm involves randomization, which is a topic in information theory (cs.IT) and machine learning (cs.LG).
